         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W. ¶ London ¶ Jany 10 /77 ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ I have to thank you for your note and am glad to hear that the Gramineae are on their way. The Shannon is due I believe in the course o...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.01.10</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS annotation by M: 'Answ 13/3/77. F.v.M.'.</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text" style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times; ">25, WILTON PLACE. S.W.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">London</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Jany 10 /77</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to thank you for your note and am glad to hear that the <name key="Gramineae">Gramineae</name> are on their way. The Shannon is due I believe in the course of next month I trust the Ferns will soon follow<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to G. Bentham, 28 November 1876.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since your <name key="Cyperaceae">Cyperaceae</name> came I have been steadily at work at them but I do not get on so fast as I expected Although I do not think it necessary to verify still less to copy without verifying the non-Australian synonymy of Kunth and Boeckeler still I am obliged to much extra Australian research in order to give the general range of Australian species many of which are much confused and Linnaeus's as well as Brown's species<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In R. Brown (1810), pp. 212-43.</p>
               </note> have been often mistaken — I have now finished <name key="Cyperus">Cyperus</name> (including <name key="Mariscus">Mariscus</name>) with 64 species, <name key="Kyllinga">Kyllinga</name> 4 species <name key="Heleocharis">Heleocharis</name> 12 sp. <name key="Scirpus">Scirpus</name> including <name key="Isolepis">Isolepis</name> 22 sp. and am far advanced in Fimbristylis in which besides <name key="Abildgaardhia">Abildgaardhia</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Abildgaardia</seg>?</p>
               </note> I include (with A. Gray) <name key="Oncostylis">Oncostylis</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Browns <name key="Arthrostyles">Arthrostyles</name> remains endemic and monotypic. I always find 6 filaments though the anthers of 3 are very deciduous and perhaps sometimes abortive from the first. The style is also very particular. The plant has been described by Boeckeler as <name key="Fimbristylis%20planiculmis">Fimbristylis planiculmis</name> — he has overlooked the stamens and Brown does not mention them he probably did not feel certain about them and did not like to commit himself — The Mauritius Ceylon and Chinese species are very different from the Australian one in structure and must either make a genus of themselves or a section of Fimbristylis — but perhaps nearing to <name key="Rhynchospora">Rhynchospora</name>. That however I leave for Indian botanists to work up.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Could you kindly let me have the last number with the title page and Index of vol VIII. of your Fragmenta<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B74.13.01 includes Additamenta as well as the index.</p>
               </note> which I never have had and which is wanting to complete my copy of the volume</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope next month to announce to you the dispatch of a return box of <name key="Cyperaceae">Cyperaceae</name>. I trust you received the copy of Gen. Pl.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Genera plantarum</seg>, i.e., Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> vol. ii. part ii which I sent in one of the boxes last summer</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yours truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>George Bentham</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron Ferd v. Mueller</p>
